{
  "texts": [
    "In general, areas with low uncertainty and strong predictions for negative HPV status demonstrated high keratinization and cells with pleomorphic nuclei.",
    "Low-uncertainty areas with strongly positive HPV status predictions tended to show tightly packed cells with monotonous nuclei and surrounding inflammatory infiltrate.",
    "Both of these observations are consistent with known histopathological associations with HPV status [78,79].",
    "Attention heatmaps were also generated using the final MIL model, as shown in Additional file 1: Fig. 10.",
    "Areas with strong, high-confidence predictions from the tile-based model were generally also weighted with high attention from the MIL model."
  ]
}